Description: DESCRIPTION: A Fabulous Vintage Dooney and Bourke 'Carrier' Cross Body Satchel! This bag was constructed in the USA with lovely All-Weather Pebbled Leather in "British Tan" crème leather, and attractive brass hardware throughout. The front flap features a rounded Dooney duck patch and pretty brass turn lock closure. The flap lifts to reveal the main spacious unlined interior with zipper pocket, six slip pocket slots, and the cotton Dooney tag at the top indicating the bag was made in the USA. On the back is a slip pocket as well. Leather strap can be worn over the shoulder or cross body, and shorter handheld on top is perfect for handheld use. The original brass fob hangs from the base of the strap. Matching hang tag included. This is a great Dooney, it is very versatile and sure to be your new favorite bag! MEASUREMENTS: Please observe measurements as items may look slightly bigger or smaller in photos. Measurements are as follows: 11" across at the widest point and 8.5" from top to bottom, 3" deep, up to 22" strap drop. CONDITION: This bag is in Good used condition. The leather is soft and supple and all seams are intact. (see pics). The interior is in good condition, a little darkening, and some pen markings to the base - just be sure to check all photos.
